codex
The probes isolate the cause: ReportLab shaping is producing a valid readable PDF, but pypdf’s default “plain” extraction inserts spaces inside the Devanagari word (`क ृ षक`). The same page extracted in pypdf’s layout mode returns the exact authoritative text (`कृषक`). This rules out pagination and source-value corruption; the validator is using the wrong extraction mode for shaped Unicode text.

I’ll keep shaping enabled and make both the renderer validation and its content-proof tests use pypdf’s layout extraction. That is the smallest fix consistent with readable Unicode output.
